#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.126"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.126:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.126:0.2"
msgid "13. Bhayavagga"
msgstr "13. Fears"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: catutthapuggalasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.126:0.3"
msgid "126. Dutiyamettāsutta"
msgstr "126. Love (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.130"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.126:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world."

msgctxt "an4.126:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.126:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā "
"viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho "
"tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā "
"vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a person meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, "
"and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way "
"above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of "
"love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and "
"ill will."

msgctxt "an4.126:1.4"
msgid ""
"So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ "
"viññāṇagataṃ te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato "
"ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati."
msgstr ""
"They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an "
"abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, "
"as empty, as not-self."

msgctxt "an4.126:1.5"
msgid ""
"So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā suddhāvāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the "
"gods of the pure abodes."

msgctxt "an4.126:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upapatti asādhāraṇā puthujjanehi."
msgstr "This rebirth is not shared with ordinary people."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.126:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo karuṇā … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a person meditates spreading a heart full of compassion … "

msgctxt "an4.126:2.2"
msgid "muditā … pe … "
msgstr "rejoicing … "

msgctxt "an4.126:2.3"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā "
"tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya "
"sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena "
"averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the "
"fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they "
"spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, "
"limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

msgctxt "an4.126:2.4"
msgid ""
"So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ "
"viññāṇagataṃ te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato "
"ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati."
msgstr ""
"They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an "
"abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, "
"as empty, as not-self."

msgctxt "an4.126:2.5"
msgid ""
"So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā suddhāvāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the "
"gods of the pure abodes."

msgctxt "an4.126:2.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upapatti asādhāraṇā puthujjanehi."
msgstr "This rebirth is not shared with ordinary people."

msgctxt "an4.126:2.7"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasminti."
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.126:2.8"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
